C)  Not really def ined — I want to hear what the lender recommends f or my situation. 
Q2: A lender presents 6 loan options in your first conversation. You: 
A)  Apply your pre-set f ilter and narrow to the 2 options that meet your criteria. 
B)  Ask them to help narrow it down to the 2 best options f or your specif ic situation. 
C)  Feel overwhelmed and ask which option most people in your situation choose. 
Q3: How do you typically handle complex decisions with many variables? 
A)  I build a decision f ramework bef ore evaluating the options. 
B)  I take notes and compare af terward, though I can sometimes get overwhelmed. 
C)  I of ten def er to whoever seems most knowledgeable about the subject. 
Scoring: Mostly C answers = Higher Risk  •  Mostly A/B answers = Lower Risk. Use your result to calibrate how much 
extra attention to give this bias. 
 
⚠  WORST-CASE SCENARIO: The Approximately $29,500 Default Decision 
THE SITUATION 
First-time buyer Jordan arrives at his pre-approval meeting with no def ined pref erences. The loan of f icer 
walks him through FHA loans, conventional loans, 30-year f ixed, 20-year f ixed, 15-year f ixed, 5/1 ARMs, 
and 7/1 ARMs — complete with buydown options on each. 
 Note: Walking into a room full of jargon and options you didn't expect is genuinely disorienting. This is not a 
knowledge gap — it's a structural challenge that any unprepared buyer would face. 
THE BIAS IN ACTION 
Overwhelmed by 14+ combinations, Jordan asks: 'What do most f irst-time buyers do?' The loan of f icer 
recommends a standard 30-year conventional at the bank's standard rate — which happens to be 0.35% 
above what Jordan would likely qualif y f or with an FHA loan given his 680 credit score and 5% down 
payment. 
THE ESTIMATED DOLLAR COST* 
Based on these illustrative assumptions: conventional at 7.1% vs. FHA at 6.75% — both 30-year f ixed 
loans on Jordan's profile — the estimated lifetime interest cost difference is approximately $29,500. Jordan 
def aulted into a less optimal loan type simply because he hadn't arrived with a comparison f ramework. 
(Important: FHA mortgage insurance premium structures are subject to change and vary by loan term and 
down payment. Consult a licensed lender for current MIP comparisons before assuming FHA is the lower-
cost option.) 
THE LESSON 
Building your loan filter before any lender meeting is one of the most protective things you can do. If  you're 
a Georgia homebuyer, Mo Phanor can help you build a clear f ramework tailored to your credit prof ile and 
goals. Call or text 404-692-2444 or visit mophanor.com. 
 
