BIAS 5  STATUS QUO BIAS 
"Loyalty to your bank is admirable. Your mortgage doesn't have to live there." 
Status quo bias is our pref erence f or the f amiliar — def aulting to existing institutions and options not because 
they're demonstrably better, but because switching f eels uncertain and ef f ortf ul. In mortgage terms, this typically 
means  choosing your existing bank without discovering what you were leaving on the table. 
 
易  SELF-ASSESSMENT QUIZ 
Q1: When you began the homebuying process, your first call was to: 
