THE 7 BIAS REMINDERS 
1. Anchoring: I arrived with the Freddie Mac average. That is my ref erence point — not their f irst quote. 
2. Present Bias: I will evaluate TOTAL interest paid, not just monthly payment. 
3. Choice Overload: I have my loan criteria. I will not evaluate options outside my f ilter today. 
4. Loss Aversion: Missing this house is not a loss. A bad loan term is. 
5. Status Quo Bias: This is one lender among several. I will compare bef ore committing. 
6. Sunk Cost: Time spent here does not obligate me to proceed. I can always restart. 
7. Recency Bias: Short-term rate or price movements do not change my timeline. I buy when I'm ready. 
 
